         <abstract id="aspace_06530216dc8adaab00f0c3fe083e8bb4">A collection of letters of the family of Henry Dutton (1796-1869), Yale College
1818, 38th governor of Connecticut and Yale law professor (1847-1869). The
letters of his only son, Henry Melzar Dutton (1838-1862), Yale College 1857
and Yale Law 1859, written while working as a lawyer in Litchfield, Connecticut,
until April 1861 and then serving as a 1st Lieutenant with Company C of the
5th Regiment of Connecticut Volunteers during the Civil War until his death
on August 9, 1862, constitute the bulk of the collection. Also included are
letters between other members of the Dutton family as well as related families;
genealogical information; and short biographies of Henry Dutton, Eliza Eliot
Dutton, and Henry Melzar Dutton. Transcriptions of most of the family letters
were created by the donor.</abstract>
